required software:

- scons
- libglew1.5-dev
- glew-utils (?)
- libglut3-dev (?)
- LLVM 2.9 final
- packetizer
- ATI APP SDK
- clc tool from former ATI Stream SDK (included in folder 'bin')

installation:

- build llvm
- build packetizer
- install stream sdk
	- place ICD registration config files in /etc/OpenCL/vendors or use christophs hack :p
	- set ATISTREAMSDKROOT and ATISTREAMSDKSAMPLESROOT environment variables to stream sdk root dir
	- build stream sdk (ignore errors related to CAL (only for SDK versions < 2.4)
- adjust 'setupenv.sh' and/or 'setupenvdebug.sh' to match your system
- source 'setupenv.sh' or 'setupenvdebug.sh' to build in opt or debug mode (= build against LLVM in debug or release mode)
- run scons, options (default shown):
	debug=0
	debug-runtime=0
	profile=0
	packetize=0 (enable packetization)
	openmp=0 (enable openmp multi threading)
	threads=0 (set number of threads to use if openmp is enabled (default: 4))
	split=0  (disable mem access optimizations)
	dynamic=0 (build dynamic driver library instead of static)

windows installation:

- copy glut32.dll and glew32.dll from lib to Windows/system32
